snippet.textDisplay:
It’s sad when people are being more of themselves in their talents and spectators don’t appreciate it. Everyone wants to be in lala land and that’s the reason entertainers present fake and unrealistic images of who they are; which drives most of them nearly if not completely insane. I understand it’s entertainment and people want to be just that. However, perhaps people should find authenticity more entertaining than being brainwashed and lied to by entertainers presenting characters rather than who they truly are.

Lastly, if you only want the fantasy side of entertainment stop being interested in what these people do in their everyday lives. Certainly know when the fantasy is over and they leave the stage grown people shouldn’t be chasing them down the street, begging for autographs and ripping at their clothes. If you don’t know where the fantasy ends and reality begins it’s not just entertainment to you. Teach these truths to your children so they can tell the difference even though many adults have no desire to. It’s time for truth to become more important to people than fantasies.

It’s Time For Real Changes—>IJS
